'''Onsen Shrine''' (温泉神社) is a {{ill|Shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shrine|qq=}} located in the hot spring town of Unzen in {{ill|Nagasaki Prefecture|ja|長崎県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagasaki Prefecture|qq=}}{{ill|Unzen City|ja|雲仙市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Unzen City|qq=}}, 小浜町雲仙319.

Managed as a {{ill|Bettōji|ja|別当寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bettōji|qq=}} under the syncretism of Shinto and Buddhism ({{ill|Shinbutsu-shūgō|ja|神仏習合|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinbutsu-shūgō|qq=}}), the hot spring mountain {{ill|Manmyōji|ja|満明寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Manmyōji|qq=}} was established<ref name="unzen2019">{{Cite journal |Language=Japanese |author1=山﨑 功 |author2=和田 奈緒 |author3=Peemmaphat BUARAPHA |author4=出口智佳子 |title=雲仙・島原史の多文化研究 II―自然が育んだ雲仙山岳信仰の源流と現在・未来― |journal= |volume= |issue= |publisher=Saga University |date=2019 |pages=39-57 |url=https://saga-u.repo.nii.ac.jp/record/22439/files/yamazaki_201903.pdf}}</ref>. “Unzen” was originally written as “Onsen” (温泉), a nomenclature said to be derived from the mountain name of Manmyōji<ref>{{Cite journal |Language=Japanese |author=池永正人 |title=観光資源としての雲仙地獄 |journal=Onsen Regional Studies |issue=12 |date=2009 |pages=13-20 |url=https://onsenchiiki.jp/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/%E7%AC%AC12%E5%8F%B7.pdf}}</ref>.

